# Writing Feedback System

- Require course staff RBAC and the `writingFeedback` course capability on every operational endpoint.
- Instructors/admins configure the capability; instructors and TAs operate it.
- Instructors/admins create, edit, and approve rubric versions; TAs may view the approved rubric but must not mutate it.
- Keep routes thin, orchestration in `src/writing-feedback/`, and persistence in the Mongo delegate.
- Model output is immutable draft provenance. Staff edits are append-only revisions.
- Approval and release are separate explicit actions; generation never releases.
- Canvas import is an explicit staff action that writes local records only. It must not create/associate a Canvas rubric, comment, or grade.
- Keep local synthetic Canvas demo, not-configured, and future live OAuth modes visibly and technically distinct.
- Missing capability configuration means disabled. Disabling never deletes assessment records.
- Never log student content, model prompts/responses, Canvas identifiers, or tokens.
